inn1.comm: and he's gone first ball! He slanted that full and wide, and he went hard at it but the ball sliced off the face of his bat and Ahmed Shehzad takes a good catch at point, diving to his right
back of a length, slanted across outside off, and Smith lets it go
back of a length, a little closer to off stump this time, Smith leaves again
fuller, wide of off stump, third leave in a row
back of a length on off and middle, defended towards mid-off
back of a length outside off, shuffles across and punches it to mid-on
short, wide, and Shehzad dives full length to his left at backward point and stops a certain boundary after Warner reached across and slapped hard at it
back of a length, angling in on an off-stump line, defended towards mid-off off the back foot
short and wide again and this time Warner finds the gap in front of backward point. Strong wrists through that square cut, there
back of a length outside off, punched to wide mid-off
fuller now, angling down the leg side, and Warner doesn't connect with his flick, and collects a leg bye after the ball runs off his pad towards deep backward square leg
length ball outside off, Smith gets a decent stride in to defend towards cover
length ball on middle stump. Warner stays in his crease and jams his bat down to poke it away towards midwicket
looks to angle it in again, and slants down the leg side. Pings him on the pad as he misses the flick
back of a length now, and he shuffles across and tucks it off his hip towards square leg
full on a fifth stump line, and Warner plays a checked drive to mid-off
length ball, a little closer to off stump, defended towards mid-off
straightens from a good length on off stump, and the ball slides off the shoulder of Warner's bat down to backward point as he looks to defend
length ball on middle and off, tucked away towards midwicket
full, a bit of width, and he presses forward and leans into a nice looking drive, straight to mid-off
back of a length on off stump, shuffles across and tucks it away backward of square leg
short, and he's back in a flash to pull that from outside off, wide of midwicket
straightens a touch outside off, just back of a length, and Warner adjusts to defend towards cover point
back of a length on off stump, defended off the back foot to cover
full, too full on a fourth-stump line, and Smith just showed a full face and drove that down the ground. Bounced over the stumps at the bowler's end and the umpire moved swiftly out of the way
full and straight, blocked towards mid-on
length ball on middle and leg, he's attacking the stumps here, and Smith clips it away to midwicket
back of a length now, angling across, teasing line, and Smith lets it go
length ball, kept low outside off, and Smith got a tiny edge on it as he jammed his bat down and the ball bounced on its way through to Sarfraz

overpitched ball, similar to the one Smith drove down the ground a few balls ago, but this time he goes a bit too hard at it, doesn't time it, and jams it down into the pitch, easily fielded by the bowler in his follow-through
full on leg stump, angling down, and Warner can't connect with the flick and is hit on the boot
length ball outside off, and he gets a decent stride out to punch that towards cover point
shortish ball, a bit of width as well, but cover point is right on the circle and he slapped that straight to the fielder
back of a length on off stump, defended off the back foot to short cover
short, wide, and this time he stands up tall and finds the gap between short extra cover and cover point
full, on the pads, clipped away to deep backward square leg. Slows down quite a lot on a patchy bit of outfield
back of a length, slanting away from Smith, and he lets it go through to the keeper
beauty! moved his length a little fuller, and Smith came forward to defend. The ball carried on with the angle, bounced a touch extra, and beat the outside edge
slower ball, very full on middle stump, flicked away towards square leg
back of a length outside off, punched to cover
back of a length on off stump, and Smith goes back, waits for it to come to him and dinks it into the on side with soft hands to steal the quick single
back of a length again, sliding down the leg side as Warner misses the flick and ricochets off his thigh pad towards square leg
big appeal for lbw as Wahab bowls it full and Warner misses another flick, but the umpire shakes his head and you can see why - it was definitely sliding down leg
back of a length outside off, punched hard to short cover
back of a length, angling in. It's flicked in the air but bounces down safely to deep backward square leg
back of a length on off stump, defended towards short cover
slips down the leg side, not too far down, but that's enough for the umpire to exercise his arms in this format
full, a bit of width, and Smith leans into a lovely cover drive and finds the gap to the right of the cover fielder
fullish ball outside off, defended down the ground
back of a length, angled across, and he defends off the back foot
back of a length, a touch too straight, and he tucks it off his pads to deep square leg
tossed up slow outside off, defended off the front foot
down the track now, driven to deep cover

what a catch! The umpire's saying it's not out! Went for the sweep, and he got something on that and Fawad dived to his right at leg slip and took a quite magnificent grab, but maybe that wasn't off bat or glove. It hit his thigh pad, but was there a bit of deflection off the face of his bat onto the thigh?
quick and flat, and Warner goes back and pushes it back to the bowler
on the pads, clipped away to deep backward square leg
back of a length outside off, and he punches it to mid-off, who's stationed fairly wide
back of a length on off stump, defended back to the bowler
back of a length outside off, pushed to short cover
uppish, but timed very nicely. It was straight, and he stayed in the crease and pushed at the ball. It popped up a touch uppishly, but went in the gap between short midwicket and mid on
pushes at a ball angled across him, on a fourth stump line, from halfway forward, and gets a thick outside edge that runs away to the third man boundary
down the pitch and throws his hands at the ball outside off, and the ball slices off the face of his bat, wide of point and runs away for four
back of a length outside off, punched to point
quickish, fullish ball outside off, defended into the covers
a touch slower now, outside off, and he comes forward to defend to short cover
shorter this time, and he stays next to the line of the ball and pushes it with a straight bat to the sweeper at deep cover point
shortish ball, pulled, or swept from a standing position, down to deep backward square leg
length ball, angled across, and he closes his bat face to work that from outside off down to deep square leg
back of a length outside off, punched to short cover
length ball outside off, driven to deep cover
short, wide, cracked hard off the back foot and Fawad has to sprint a long way to his left from deep cover point to stop that on the slide
back of a length on off stump, and he opens his bat face and dabs that to backward point
length ball, angling across towards middle and off, worked away with a closed bat face to deep backward square leg
tossed up on middle stump, and Warner poked that with soft hands towards cover point
shortish ball, a bit of width, slapped to deep cover
full on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
quickish ball on the pads, tucked away to square leg
flat, quick, shortish, pulled to deep midwicket
fullish ball on off and middle, defended to short cover
back of a length, just outside off, punched to mid-off
length ball on off stump, tight line, defended off the back foot, back to the bowler
length ball on middle stump, clipped away. Fawad dives to his left at short midwicket to make a good stop, but can't prevent the single
fullish ball on off stump. Smith shuffles across and clips it away to deep square leg
shot! That was full and wide, slower ball as well, and he used a lot of bottom hand to swat that over mid-off
that bottom hand again. This time, it's back of a length, and he uses his hands and wrists to whip it away from outside off down to deep backward square leg
length ball on the pads, tucked away straight to square leg

appeal for caught behind, down the leg side. Looked to glance, and Sarfraz grabbed it against his thigh, on the second attempt. Umpire was unmoved. Yup, went off the pad, and Misbah did well not to review
swept away from a leg-stump line, down to deep backward square leg
down the pitch, nice footwork, checked drive down to long-off
down the leg side again, and he gets a top-edge on that sweep, goes quite uppish, quite fine, and Fawad runs across from deep backward square to stop that
back of a length, worked away to square leg, where Shehzad dives to his right to make the stop
down the pitch, makes a bit of room, and he launches this way over wide long-off with a full follow-through
back of a length on off stump, shuffles across and nurdles it away to deep square leg
back of a length outside off, poked to short cover
slower bouncer, and Warner was back very quickly and had to wait a long time before it came on and he could hook it away down to deep backward square leg
short, the regular short ball this time, and Smith swivels on it to pull it down to deep backward square leg
shortish ball, controlled, wristy pull from off stump towards deep midwicket
tossed up delivery outside off, driven to long off
full around middle, worked down to long on for one
flatter one on a length, he punches to the sweeper off the back foot
flights it a bit around off stump line, he plays it out from the crease
a quicker one that hurries after pitching and Warner jabs at it off the back foot, to short third man
played out to midwicket
he walks across before the ball is bowled, and picks this full ball from just outside off, and whips it to the deep midwicket boundary, that is some timing on this outfield
another one pitched up, and slanted across, he drives hard but sweeper is around
tries to short-arm pull this short of a length ball, but mistimes it to midwicket
punches nicely this time from the crease but picks out extra cover
short and wide, Warner sets himself up and goes hard on the cut, but hasn;t timed it well enough to beat the sweeper running to his right
four more, Smith swivels and sends this short ball racing to the deep backward square rope, fine leg wasn't too far, but he had no chance
the breakthrough, Afridi does it, Warner backs away to pull, but hits it low to midwicket, who snaps it up happily

lbw appeal first ball, and that looked very close. Not given, but he was on the front foot, and that slid on with the angle, in typically Afridi fashion, and where did that make contact? Misbah's called for the review... inside edge, was there? And was it bat first or pad first? Looked like bat first, and the umpire's decision stands
full outside leg, clipped away towards deep midwicket
shortish ball on off stump, makes some room and slaps it to deep cover
quickish ball on middle and leg, and he goes deep in his crease to tuck that away towards deep backward square leg
another quick slider, very straight, and Bailey defends carefully off the front foot
full on leg stump, clipped away to deep backward square leg
back of a length outside off, slapped away to deep cover
length ball, angled across on a fourth-stump line, and Smith comes forward to defend towards mid-off
full-toss outside off, driven to deep cover
back of a length, a bit of bounce as he looks to steer it behind point, and the ball goes uppishly in the direction of where third slip would be, but who has a third slip in ODIs?
fullish ball, angled across, and Bailey lets it go outside off
quickish down the leg side, and Irfan does brilliantly to throw himself to his right at short fine leg and stop that tickled shot
length ball outside off, defended to short cover
slides on with the angle as he comes forward to defend, goes off the inside half of his bat into the on side
quick and flat again, and he comes forward and defends towards midwicket
fullish ball on middle stump, clipped away to wide long-on
full ball on leg stump, pushed to long-on with a straight bat
short ball, angling across Smith, who walks across and miscues that pull, a touch uppish, down towards deep midwicket
length ball on a fourth-stump line, defended to mid-off
slower ball, in the blockhole on off stump, jammed back to the bowler with a straight bat
full outside off, driven to mid-off
back of a length, angled across, punched away to the right of the diving fielder at point
back of a length outside off, punched to backward point
fullish ball on leg stump, clipped away to deep backward square leg
length ball on off stump, defended towards mid-off
length ball on middle stump, pushes at it and the ball goes uppishly, just wide of Afridi, who dives to his right
full on middle stump, driven down to long-on to bring up Smith's first ODI fifty
length ball, a little slower, just outside off, and he defends into the covers
quicker now, slanted towards leg stump, dinked into the on side
tossed up outside off, driven to deep cover
short ball, pulled away to deep midwicket
tossed up from wide of the crease, wide of off stump, driven to deep cover
tossed up just outside off, driven down to long-off
length ball outside off, driven to the right of deep cover
flatter now, angled in towards leg stump. Smith stays back and pushes it to long-on with a straight bat
tossed up wide outside off, and he stays back and slaps this to mid-off. Didn't quite come on, and he may have been looking to go squarer
flicks this uppishly, against the turn, and it drops just short of Misbah, diving to his right at short midwicket
a bit of turn now, and he looks to turn it away with a closed face and the leading edge nearly carries back to the bowler
back of a length on leg and middle, and he goes back and nurdles it away towards short fine leg
short and wide, and Shehzad dives to his left at backward point to stop a well-struck cut from Bailey
back of a length, punched down the ground, and he runs an overthrow after Afridi picks up the ball and flicks the ball towards the stumps at the bowler's end
skips down the track and drives this to long-off
a very slow, round-arm ball, a la Yuvraj, and he drives towards long-off again
quicker, not as full, defended towards cover point
and now Bailey has had enough of this old-fashioned milking. Goes down on one knee and slog-sweeps him from off stump, high over deep midwicket

goes for a repeat, and Afridi does the star-man pose after taking a blinder. That wasn't quite as full, and it turned away and he hit it way up in the air. Afridi turned back from short midwicket and ran towards the 30-yard circle and tumbled forward as the ball dropped into his hands from over his shoulder
flattish ball on leg stump, clipped away to the left of deep square leg
short, wide, and this time Shehzad can't quite reach the ball as he dives to his right to stop that cut. Deep cover does the fielding behind him
flattish ball on off stump, Maxwell comes forward and opens his bat face to carve that away towards deep cover point
length ball on leg stump, and he goes on the back foot to work it away towards deep backward square leg
dropped. That turned away just a touch from a lovely length as Maxwell pushed at it in front of his body .The outside edge bounced off Sarfraz's gloves
beaten again. This one was bowled from wider on the crease, and it straightened and was a little too quick for Maxwell
slower, fuller, straighter, and Maxwell turns it carefully to short midwicket
length ball outside off, driven to long-off
tossed up on middle and off, whipped away down to long-on
tossed up again, on off stump, driven with a straight bat to long-off
flatter now, angled in towards off stump, and he works his wrists to beat Fawad, who sprinted to his right in his follow-through to try and cut off the single
tossed up outside off, and Maxwell didn't get to the pitch of it. The ball turns, takes his outside edge, and runs away towards the third man boundary
shortish ball outside off, steered away to deep cover point

dropped again! Maxwell looks to slog against the turn from wide outside off, and the edge loops up behind the stumps. Shehzad runs back very quickly from wide slip and gets his hands to it but the ball bounces out
full on leg stump, clipped down to long on
back of a length outside off, punched away to deep point
down the pitch now, and flicked against the turn towards deep midwicket
angled in from wide of the crease, turns away from a nice length on off stump, and Smith defends watchfully back to the bowler
back of a length on the pads, clipped away wide of mid-on
back of a length outside off, punched to deep cover point
length ball, hit on the pads as he missed the flick. Pitched outside leg
back of a length on middle stump, shuffles across and works it to deep square leg
back of a length just outside off, and he slices it down to third man
back of a length on middle and off. Shuffles across but can't get it past short midwicket
angled in to the pad, worked to midwicket
flighted, straightening on middle, defended
eases a flighted ball past extra cover to the sweeper
could have been in trouble, skipped out and chipped it over midwicket, fell short of long on running across
defended off the front foot
reverse sweep to end the over, picks up the full ball from around off and cracks it past short third
length ball worked off the pad to deep square leg
a slower bouncer, he walks across and lets it travel down the leg side
length ball on middle, whipped to deep midwicket
tries to drive but checks his shot to mid off as this is not full enough
opens the face and runs this length ball to third man
slower ball pitched up on the stumps, blocked back
width on this length ball, cracked away to the sweeper

this time he is gone, skips out, and lofts it, he didn't appear to be sure what to do with it, and appeared to have got a touch too close to the pitch, Irfan does not make any mistake as he slides to take it at long off
defended softly off the front foot
goes on the back foot, makes some room, and punches to point
walks out of the crease and works it to deep square leg
length ball played out to midwicket
tossed up delivery, he moves forward and runs it to backward point
short of a length, tapped to point
back of a length ball punched to the sweeper
poor line, down the pads, and he tickles it fine past the keeper
length ball, he moves forward and blocks
works it in front of square off middle, and they settle for one
shortish ball worked softly to the right of midwicket
came in with the angle but slowly enough to be punched off the back foot to extra cover
leaves the crease but misses the whip and is hit on the pad
backs away again to one that is pitched up and coming on towards the stumps, punches it back to bowler's left, he cannot stop it
pushes in front of point, nonstriker wants the single, sent back
takes a thick edge as he defends from the crease, and runs to point
pushes off the front foot to the bowler
turns a short of a length ball to midwicket
short and wide, he tries to force it away, but mishits, Alam at extra cover flies to his right, and takes pace off it
taps a pitched up ball on the off side, and they scamper through, would have been trouble had bowler picked the ball up cleanly
forces a back of a length ball to long on past midwicket's dive
wanted to have a go at this pitched up wide ball but it was the slower one and he had to tap it to point
slowish back of a length ball played out to backward point
tossed up delivery pushed to the off side
comes forward again and pushes to extra cover
quicker and angled in on middle, turned to midwicket
punched off the back foot to long off
turned off the pad to square leg
nudged behind square leg for a single
pitched up ball on off stump pushed to mid off
works a back of a length ball behind square to Irfan, who stops it with his foot
was preparing to have a crack at this one but was cramped for room and tapped it onto the crease for one
flays at this one with slight width but hits it to short third
sends this 146.6 kph length ball down the leg side
walks outside off stump, he goes full outside off, is pushed to extra cover
works it off the pad to deep square leg
he's been itching to have a crack, does it this time, down the track, to the pitch and launches it powerfully straight down the ground
backs away but punches it straight to the bowler
walks out, but is too close to the pitch, and pats it back
on the back foot again to punch to long off
hit hard down to long off
length ball on off stump, punched to long on
punches a good length ball to extra cover
he's fetched this from outside off, and used his wrists to send it behind square leg
could have disappeared, but Smith has flicked this off his pad straight to short fine leg
neat, firm drive drive, but Alam is hard to get past at extra cover, he dives and stops it
length ball around off stump turned to midwicket
pushes it down the ground, mid off runs around and fields
starts with a short ball, and Smith picks the gap to the right of long on with a pull
goes much slower through midwicket now, but fielder runs in and keeps them to one

a much fuller delivery and Afridi has another, but Faulkner will review, tossed up ball, dipping and drifting in, Faulkner pushes forward, the impact is pad first, on middle and off, ball tracker says that is hitting the inside of off, and Faulkner will walk back
whoa, he gives him a fast one, short and wide, and Haddin cuts that to the third man boundary
worked off the pad in front of square
opens the face and guides this length ball to Shehzad, who stops it at point with a dive
short and wide, hit to the right of the sweeper
drives to the sweeper off the front foot
short and wide, he's glided it nicely, but picked out backward point
runs this fine just past the keeper to third man
taps a length ball for a single to cover
hundred for Smith, works it from outside off to midwicket, trots across, gets a pat on the back from Afridi before he raises his bat, first century, and in such tough conditions
defended off the front foot
angled in to middle, tapped back to the bowler
worked through midwicket, they hesitate for an instant as they see the fielder charge in from the deep, the throw comes in at the keeper's end, but Haddin has just made it
shot, a flighted ball, and he comes forward to flay it through the covers
full one worked down to long on
tries to tap this short of a length ball to third man but is beaten as it bounces past
another short one, Haddin manages to whack it over extra cover as it bounces at him, pulled back just inside the rope
a slower one slanted across, he swings and misses
hit away for a single towards midwicket
a slower one pitched up to the stumps, blocked back
length ball on the pads, but Haddin cannot connect as he tries to flick
charges out, Afridi bowls it full and wide, Smith reaches out and slams it straight to long off
goes back to defend a length ball to the bowler
turned off the pad behind square leg
googly, pulled down to long on
full and angled in, turned to short fine leg
steps out, swings and misses this length ball outside off, Riaz gives him a long stare
good length on off, squeezed out to backward point
very full and he opens the face to lift it over point, sweeper is around to stop it
has a go at this length ball, it runs through midwicket
another one, he charges out, and wants to deposit this short of a length ball down the ground, but only hits it as far as long on
short of a length ball rises and hits him as he fails to work it away
gets a yorker in on the stumps, it is squeezed out to midwicket
took his eyes off this, it wasn't too short, but kept rising into him, and pinged the glove
was making some room but Irfan banged it in short, it came at his throat, and Johnson just got out of the way in time
short again, but leg sidish, and Johnson flays it down to the fine leg boundary
slower one outside off as he walks across and turns it to deep square
another slower one, he makes some room and has a crack at it, mishits to extra cover
backs away outside leg, Riaz follows him with a yorker, and he misses it
a pretty high full toss now, slips just down leg
backs away to leg, but misses a length delivery just outside off stump
length ball on off stump, he walks across and turns it to fine leg
shot, mid off is up, this one is pitched up, and Haddin has lofted it very cleanly over the fielder
141 kph back of a length ball, he tries to pull, but there is no room and he plays it to midwicket
short of a length on the pad, he tries to force it fine but cannot do much with it
a slower length ball just outside off, Haddin tries to heave it away and misses
short of a length and climbing outside off, Haddin tries to launch it over extra cover, misses again
short of a length, guided to point
a slower one again, Johnson misses as he walks across, Irfan thought there was something there
makes room outside leg but Irfan is on target with a yorker and it is through Johnson again
a high full toss, Johnson is surprised, and only manages to stab it away, close to being a no-ball for height but not quite
pitched up ball flayed off an inside edge to deep square
full and Johnson has got hold of this, he's clobbered it past Riaz, who is lucky not to get hit
a full toss now, he walks across and whips it square for four more
three in a row, Johnso backs away, Riaz keeps it outside off, Johnson reaches it to guide it past covers
short of a length, worked through square leg for two more
bouncer outside off, climbing too much, says square leg umpire, that is an unfair call
Riaz on target finally this over, Johnson makes room, swings and misses, and Riaz hits leg stump with a length ball
makes room and slices this length ball wide of the sweeper for two

inn2.comm: length delivery at 140kph angling away outside off, left alone by Shehzad
back of length right on the stumps with some inswing, thick outside edge runs down to third man for one
welcomes him with a bouncer towards the shoulders, Sarfraz takes his eyes off the ball and manages a glove towards short fine leg
angles this across the batsman from just outside off by pitching on length, Shehzad pushed and missed
fuller and wider outside off, left alone this time
swings this one down the leg side from length for a wide
short ball but it's not a bouncer, Shehzad stays back and pulls it over midwicket for two. He didn't middle that or it would have easily gone for four
swings this in a long way from outside off, Sarfraz is stuck to the crease and is hit on the frint pad for a loud appeal, but the umpire says no. Might have hit just outside off
run-out chance this time! The short of length ball jabbed in again, he pushed towards midwicket and wanted a single but Shehzad said no, had the fielder got a direct hit, he was gone
way outside off from back of length, left for a wide
full on the pads, flicked down to fine leg for one but it's off the pad
short of length outside off without any swing, pushed to point
fuller and wider, easily left for another wide
brings it in now from back of length outside off, Shehzad defends it back
touch fuller outside off on length, thick edge goes to third man for one
length ball outside off, driven firmly straight to cover
goes for a swing and edges to slip! The length ball with room outside off made Shehzad drive hard at it, he got a thick edge and it went straight to Smith at second slip at waist height
short ball on the pads, runs it down to fine leg off the thigh pad

short delivery, oh that's too short and that's gone over the keeper! It attained height after crossing the batsman after pitching outside off, and went for four byes. The umpire initially thought it went off the bat and had to change his decision
teasing line outside off with the angle, he drives and misses
fuller on the pads, tucked to square leg
short ball outside off, extra bounce takes the top of the bat to go to third man
jabs it in from short of length outside off, Sarfraz adjusts in time to cut it to second slip after a bounce
not as much movement this time, it was well outside off and maybe he expected it to come in so ended up chasing it and missed
fuller delivery outside off, pushed to cover point softly
keeps it full, it's driven handsomely towards the covers and Bailey dives to his right from cover point to stop it with one hand
back to short of length, he stays back and plays it late, but dangerously, as it was very close to a diving Smith at second slip. Went just wide and beat third man too for a four
nearly a yorker on middle stump, driven off the back foot wide of mid-on for two
good-length ball just outside off, defends it to point
hint of inswing after it pitched on length outside off, pushed back to the bowler
length ball angling away this time outside off, pushed to cover point off the back foot
bangs in a bouncer around middle stump, he ducks under it
in the block hole outside off, inside edge hits the pads and that's only two from the over
swings it in from outside off, Sarfraz defends off the front foot towards cover
comes down the track and across, pull-whips it to the fine-leg area for two as Faulkner cuts it in time
slightly full on the off stump, he pushes it back to the bowler
charges down again, Kane bangs it in and he's hit on the helmet while pulling and the ball goes to point
length ball with room, runs it late just wide of third man for two more
brings it in a bit from length outside off, pushed to point without much footwork
full on the pads, tucked easily to deep midwicket for one
angled across this time off length, Sarfraz chased and missed
slightly shorter around off with the angle, pushed to cover this time. No time for a run
back of length outside off, he defends softly and the ball rolls away to the keeper

charges down and what was that!! He just swept Faulkner for six and that's gone over the roof! The ball wasn't full but he came down and down on one knee, slog-swept the ball from jsut outside off for a massive six
slower one now but it's down leg for a wide
short of length and angling away, cuts it late to third man for one
fullish delivery outside off, driven nicely to point
bangs it in outside off, Sarfraz took a step down but that had some extra bounce to go over the bat
back of length around off, he stays back this time and a thickish edge flies towards cover
141kph, on length just outside off, plays it late to run it to third man
back of length ball on middle is clipped to fine leg off the back foot for one
another short of length ball outside off, cuts it late to third man for one more
takes a step down and sweeps him again! Fine leg was in and he hit it well enough to sweep it along the ground, just wide of the fielder in the circle for four
the reply is a bouncer from Faulkner. He had to stay back for this one to defend it
bit of room and it's short of length outside off, he cuts it late, trying to beat third man for four but Abbot slides to his left to save two runs
right on target on middle stump on length, solid defence from Sarfraz
comes down the track and makes it a full toss on the pads to flick it past square leg for four more! He's turning the pressure back on Faulkner and Australia
back of length on leg stump, clipped softly towards midwicket for one and he keeps the strike
